	<div class="dropdown">
		<button class="dropbtn">Frequently-Asked Vocabulary</button>
  <div class="dropdown-content">
    <a >Virus - a type of germ that can make you sick when they enter your body. </a>
    <a >Cells - small living things that make up your body. Every living thing is made up of cells. </a>
    <a>Coronavirus - a type of virus with a spiky outer layer that makes it easier to stick to cells.  </a>
    <a>COVID-19 - the current version of the coronavirus that is causing this pandemic. The 'CO' stands for 'corona,' the 'VI' stands for 'virus,' the 'D' stands for 'disease.' The 19 refers to the year of this type of coronavirus, 2019. </a>
    <a>Pandemic - When referring to a disease, it is the outbreak of a disease that is affecting a large amount of people world-wide. </a>
    <a>Quarantine - it refers to isolating, or staying alone, from others to avoid the spread of disease. </a>
    <a>Contagion - the spreading of disease through close contact. </a>
    <a>Vaccine - a creation that acts like a disease on a smaller scale so that your body builds strength and is able to remain immune to the real virus. </a>
    <a>Immune - resistant to a particular infection. </a>
  </div>
  </div>
