      <h3 style="text-align:center">The Procedure</h3>
      <p style="text-align:center">Staying clean and preventing the spread of disease is the greatest way to stay safe during COVID-19. Play the hygeine choice game below to find the best way to stay clean. 
        <hr noshade>
      </p>
      
      <p style="text-align:center"> <i> HOW TO PLAY: click the option under the question that you think is the right answer. </i> </p> 
      
          
      <p><b> 
        1. You just sneezed into your arm. Do you wash your hands?</b></p>
        <p id="cor1" onclick="myFunction()">a) Yes.</p>
        <p id="fal1" onclick="myFunction()"">b) No.</p>
        
<script>
function myFunction() {
  document.getElementById("cor1").innerHTML = "✔ Yes is Correct! Always wash your hands after sneezing or coughing!";
   document.getElementById("fal1").innerHTML = "No is Wrong!";
}
</script>
<p><b> 
  2. You are at the sink. Approximately how long should you scrub your hands for?</b> </p>
        <p id="fal2" onclick="myFunction2()">a) 10 seconds.</p>
        <p id="cor2" onclick="myFunction2()">b) 20 seconds.</p>
<script>
function myFunction2() {
  document.getElementById("cor2").innerHTML = "✔ 20 seconds is Correct! Wash thoroughly with soap and water for at least 20 seconds. Sing the 'Happy Birthday' song twice as a way of checking.";
   document.getElementById("fal2").innerHTML = "10 seconds is Wrong!"
}
</script>
<p><b>  3. You just touched a door handle that many other people have touched. What do you do? </b></p>
        <p id="fal3" onclick="myFunction3()">a) Use hand sanitizer.</p>
        <p id="cor3" onclick="myFunction3()">b) Wash my hands.</p>
        <p id="fal4" onclick="myFunction3()">c) Either hand sanitize or wash my hands since they are the same.</p>
<script>
function myFunction3() {
  document.getElementById("cor3").innerHTML = "✔ Ideally, washing your hands is best!";
   document.getElementById("fal3").innerHTML = "Hand sanitizing is acceptable when there is no access to soap and water but hand washing is preferred."
   document.getElementById("fal4").innerHTML = "Hand sanitizer is not the same as washing with soap and water!"
}
</script>
<p> <b>
  4. Should you wear a mask when near other people?</b> </p>
        <p id="fal5" onclick="myFunction4()">a) No, You don't need to wear a mask if you aren't feeling sick.  </p>
        <p id="cor4" onclick="myFunction4()">b) Yes.</p>
<script>
function myFunction4() {
  document.getElementById("cor4").innerHTML = "✔ Always wear a mask when near people you haven't been quarantined with! Masks greatly reduce the chance of picking up or spreading germs from sneezes and coughs.";
   document.getElementById("fal5").innerHTML = "Even if you don't feel sick, still wear a mask! That way, you won't pick up germs from other people."
}
   </script>
