<p style="text-align:center"> Keep these rules in mind to maximize your chance of killing germs and reduce the spread of contagion! Remember: avoid touching your face, keep at least 6 feet of distance between you and other people when outside, and follow safety precautions at all times! As a child of a healthcare worker, your parent is on the frontlines and could possibly bring contagion with them. If they ask you to stay with another relative, understand that they only want you to stay healthy! If you want to learn more facts about COVID-19, grab and trusted adult and click on the image below to be redirected to the official Center for Disease Control's (CDC) website.
  </p>
<a href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/index.html?s_cid=bb-coronavirus-2019-ncov-NCIRD" title="image of SARS-CoV-2"><img src="https://www.canada.ca/content/dam/news/carousel/20200313-en-1170x347.jpg" style="width:300px; height:100px; border:0px;" alt="image of Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19)"/></a>
